 <foreign xml:lang="gez">ባሕረ፡ ሊባ፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> bāḥra libā </quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> northwest </quote></cit> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወእመ፡ ይትከሀሎሙ፡ ይብጽሑ፡ ፊንቄ፡ ወይክ(ር)ሙ፡ ውስተ፡ ቀሬጤ፡ ዘአንጻረ፡ ባሕረ፡ ሊባ፡</foreign> ‘<cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><quote> if it were possible for them, to reach Phoenicia and winter in Crete, which is facing northwest (?) </quote></cit>’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Getatchew2013MeshafeBerhanT"/><citedRange unit="page"> 73 (ed.)</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><ptr target="bm:Getatchew2013MeshafeBerhanV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 50 (tr.)</citedRange></bibl> (‘In some sources, <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> baḥr </quote></cit> and <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> liba </quote></cit> refer to opposite directions, the former to northeast and the latter to southwest. In others <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> baḥr </quote></cit> is southwest and <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> liba </quote></cit> northwest. How “<cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote> baḥrä liba </quote></cit>” stood for “northwest” (<foreign xml:lang="grc">χῶρος</foreign>) is not clear.’ <bibl><ptr target="bm:Getatchew2013MeshafeBerhanV"/><citedRange unit="page"> 50 n. 233</citedRange></bibl>) <lbl expand="videas">vid.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሊባ፡</foreign> <sense n="G" xml:id="TG"> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ባሕር፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>bāḥr</quote></cit>, <lbl expand="pluralis">Pl.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">አብሕርት፡</foreign> <cit type="transcription" xml:lang="gez"><quote>ʾabḥǝrt</quote></cit> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote>mare</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote>lacus</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la"><quote>flumen</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>mer</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>lac</quote></cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="fr"><quote>fleuve</quote></cit> Ms. Roma, Biblioteca Nazionale Centrale di Roma, Orientale 134, p. 66. <lb/>
